6168  /*************************************************************************
6169  Dense solver for A*X=B with N*N symmetric positive definite matrix A given
6170  by its Cholesky decomposition, and N*M vectors X and B. It is "slow-but-
6171  feature-rich" version of the solver which estimates condition number of
6172  the system.
6173 
6174  Algorithm features:
6175  * automatic detection of degenerate cases
6176  * O(M*N^2) complexity
6177  * condition number estimation
6178  * matrix is represented by its upper or lower triangle
6179 
6180  No iterative refinement is provided because such partial representation of
6181  matrix does not allow efficient calculation of extra-precise matrix-vector
6182  products for large matrices. Use RMatrixSolve or RMatrixMixedSolve if you
6183  need iterative refinement.
6184 
6185  IMPORTANT: ! this function is NOT the most efficient linear solver provided
6186  ! by ALGLIB. It estimates condition number of linear system,
6187  ! which results in significant performance penalty when
6188  ! compared with "fast" version which just calls triangular
6189  ! solver. Amount of overhead introduced depends on M (the
6190  ! larger - the more efficient).
6191  !
6192  ! This performance penalty is insignificant when compared with
6193  ! cost of large LU decomposition. However, if you call this
6194  ! function many times for the same left side, this overhead
6195  ! BECOMES significant. It also becomes significant for small-
6196  ! scale problems (N<50).
6197  !
6198  ! In such cases we strongly recommend you to use faster solver,
6199  ! SPDMatrixCholeskySolveMFast() function.
6200 
6201  INPUT PARAMETERS
6202  CHA - array[0..N-1,0..N-1], Cholesky decomposition,
6203  SPDMatrixCholesky result
6204  N - size of CHA
6205  IsUpper - what half of CHA is provided
6206  B - array[0..N-1,0..M-1], right part
6207  M - right part size
6208 
6209  OUTPUT PARAMETERS
6210  Info - return code:
6211  * -3 A is is exactly singular or badly conditioned
6212  X is filled by zeros in such cases.
6213  * -1 N<=0 was passed
6214  * 1 task was solved
6215  Rep - additional report, following fields are set:
6216  * rep.r1 condition number in 1-norm
6217  * rep.rinf condition number in inf-norm
6218  X - array[N]:
6219  * for info>0 contains solution
6220  * for info=-3 filled by zeros
6221 
6222  -- ALGLIB --
6223  Copyright 27.01.2010 by Bochkanov Sergey
6224  *************************************************************************/
6225  public static void spdmatrixcholeskysolvem(double[,] cha,
6226  int n,

6228  double[,] b,
6229  int m,
6230  ref int info,
6231  densesolverreport rep,
6232  ref double[,] x,
6233  alglib.xparams _params)
6234  {
6235  double[,] emptya = new double[0,0];
6236 
6237  info = 0;
6238  x = new double[0,0];
6239 
6240 
6241  //
6242  // prepare: check inputs, allocate space...
6243  //
6244  if( n<=0 || m<=0 )
6245  {
6246  info = -1;
6247  return;
6248  }
6249 
6250  //
6251  // solve
6252  //
6253  spdmatrixcholeskysolveinternal(cha, n, isupper, emptya, false, b, m, ref info, rep, ref x, _params);
6254  }

6258  Dense solver for A*X=B with N*N symmetric positive definite matrix A given
6259  by its Cholesky decomposition, and N*M vectors X and B. It is "fast-but-
6260  lightweight" version of the solver which just solves linear system,
6261  without any additional functions.

6264  * O(M*N^2) complexity
6265  * matrix is represented by its upper or lower triangle
6266  * no additional functionality

6270  SPDMatrixCholesky result

6275

6277  Info - return code:
6278  * -3 A is is exactly singular or badly conditioned
6279  X is filled by zeros in such cases.

6281  * 1 task was solved

6283  * for info>0 overwritten by solution
6284  * for info=-3 filled by zeros

6289  public static void spdmatrixcholeskysolvemfast(double[,] cha,

6291  bool isupper,
6292  double[,] b,

6294  ref int info,
6295  alglib.xparams _params)
6296  {
6297  int i = 0;
6298  int j = 0;
6299  int k = 0;
6300 
6301  info = 0;
6302 
6303  info = 1;
6304  if( n<=0 )
6305  {
6306  info = -1;
6307  return;
6308  }
6309  for(k=0; k<=n-1; k++)
6310  {
6311  if( (double)(cha[k,k])==(double)(0.0) )
6312  {
6313  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
6314  {
6315  for(j=0; j<=m-1; j++)
6316  {
6317  b[i,j] = 0.0;
6318  }
6319  }
6320  info = -3;
6321  return;
6322  }
6323  }
6324  if( isupper )
6325  {
6326  ablas.rmatrixlefttrsm(n, m, cha, 0, 0, true, false, 1, b, 0, 0, _params);
6327  ablas.rmatrixlefttrsm(n, m, cha, 0, 0, true, false, 0, b, 0, 0, _params);
6328  }
6329  else
6330  {
6331  ablas.rmatrixlefttrsm(n, m, cha, 0, 0, false, false, 0, b, 0, 0, _params);
6332  ablas.rmatrixlefttrsm(n, m, cha, 0, 0, false, false, 1, b, 0, 0, _params);
6333  }
6334  }

6337  /*************************************************************************
6338  Dense solver for A*x=b with N*N symmetric positive definite matrix A given
6339  by its Cholesky decomposition, and N*1 real vectors x and b. This is "slow-
6340  but-feature-rich" version of the solver which, in addition to the
6341  solution, performs condition number estimation.
6342 
6343  Algorithm features:
6344  * automatic detection of degenerate cases
6345  * O(N^2) complexity
6346  * condition number estimation
6347  * matrix is represented by its upper or lower triangle
6348 
6349  No iterative refinement is provided because such partial representation of
6350  matrix does not allow efficient calculation of extra-precise matrix-vector
6351  products for large matrices. Use RMatrixSolve or RMatrixMixedSolve if you
6352  need iterative refinement.
6353 
6354  IMPORTANT: ! this function is NOT the most efficient linear solver provided
6355  ! by ALGLIB. It estimates condition number of linear system,
6356  ! which results in 10-15x performance penalty when compared
6357  ! with "fast" version which just calls triangular solver.
6358  !
6359  ! This performance penalty is insignificant when compared with
6360  ! cost of large LU decomposition. However, if you call this
6361  ! function many times for the same left side, this overhead
6362  ! BECOMES significant. It also becomes significant for small-
6363  ! scale problems (N<50).
6364  !
6365  ! In such cases we strongly recommend you to use faster solver,
6366  ! SPDMatrixCholeskySolveFast() function.
6367 
6368  INPUT PARAMETERS
6369  CHA - array[N,N], Cholesky decomposition,
6370  SPDMatrixCholesky result
6371  N - size of A
6372  IsUpper - what half of CHA is provided
6373  B - array[N], right part
6374 
6375  OUTPUT PARAMETERS
6376  Info - return code:
6377  * -3 A is is exactly singular or ill conditioned
6378  X is filled by zeros in such cases.
6379  * -1 N<=0 was passed
6380  * 1 task is solved
6381  Rep - additional report, following fields are set:
6382  * rep.r1 condition number in 1-norm
6383  * rep.rinf condition number in inf-norm
6384  X - array[N]:
6385  * for info>0 - solution
6386  * for info=-3 - filled by zeros
6387 
6388  -- ALGLIB --
6389  Copyright 27.01.2010 by Bochkanov Sergey
6390  *************************************************************************/
6391  public static void spdmatrixcholeskysolve(double[,] cha,
6392  int n,
6393  bool isupper,
6394  double[] b,
6395  ref int info,
6396  densesolverreport rep,
6397  ref double[] x,
6398  alglib.xparams _params)
6399  {
6400  double[,] bm = new double[0,0];
6401  double[,] xm = new double[0,0];
6402  int i_ = 0;
6403 
6404  info = 0;
6405  x = new double[0];
6406 
6407  if( n<=0 )
6408  {
6409  info = -1;
6410  return;

6414  {
6415  bm[i_,0] = b[i_];
6416  }
6417  spdmatrixcholeskysolvem(cha, n, isupper, bm, 1, ref info, rep, ref xm, _params);
6418  x = new double[n];

6420  {
6421  x[i_] = xm[i_,0];
6422  }
6423  }

6426  /*************************************************************************
6427  Dense solver for A*x=b with N*N symmetric positive definite matrix A given
6428  by its Cholesky decomposition, and N*1 real vectors x and b. This is "fast-
6429  but-lightweight" version of the solver.
6430 
6431  Algorithm features:
6432  * O(N^2) complexity
6433  * matrix is represented by its upper or lower triangle
6434  * no additional features

6437  CHA - array[N,N], Cholesky decomposition,
6438  SPDMatrixCholesky result
6439  N - size of A
6440  IsUpper - what half of CHA is provided
6441  B - array[N], right part
6442 
6443  OUTPUT PARAMETERS
6444  Info - return code:
6445  * -3 A is is exactly singular or ill conditioned
6446  X is filled by zeros in such cases.
6447  * -1 N<=0 was passed
6448  * 1 task is solved
6449  B - array[N]:
6450  * for info>0 - overwritten by solution
6451  * for info=-3 - filled by zeros

6456  public static void spdmatrixcholeskysolvefast(double[,] cha,
6457  int n,
6458  bool isupper,
6459  double[] b,
6460  ref int info,
6461  alglib.xparams _params)
6462  {
6463  int i = 0;
6464  int k = 0;
6465 
6466  info = 0;
6467 
6468  info = 1;
6469  if( n<=0 )
6470  {
6471  info = -1;
6472  return;
6473  }
6474  for(k=0; k<=n-1; k++)
6475  {
6476  if( (double)(cha[k,k])==(double)(0.0) )
6477  {
6478  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
6479  {
6480  b[i] = 0.0;
6481  }
6482  info = -3;
6483  return;
6484  }
6485  }
6486  spdbasiccholeskysolve(cha, n, isupper, b, _params);
6487  }

6490  /*************************************************************************
6491  Dense solver for A*X=B, with N*N Hermitian positive definite matrix A and
6492  N*M complex matrices X and B. "Slow-but-feature-rich" version of the
6493  solver.
6494 
6495  Algorithm features:
6496  * automatic detection of degenerate cases
6497  * condition number estimation
6498  * O(N^3+M*N^2) complexity
6499  * matrix is represented by its upper or lower triangle
6500 
6501  No iterative refinement is provided because such partial representation of
6502  matrix does not allow efficient calculation of extra-precise matrix-vector
6503  products for large matrices. Use RMatrixSolve or RMatrixMixedSolve if you
6504  need iterative refinement.
6505 
6506  IMPORTANT: ! this function is NOT the most efficient linear solver provided
6507  ! by ALGLIB. It estimates condition number of linear system,
6508  ! which results in significant performance penalty when
6509  ! compared with "fast" version which just calls triangular
6510  ! solver.
6511  !
6512  ! This performance penalty is especially apparent when you use
6513  ! ALGLIB parallel capabilities (condition number estimation is
6514  ! inherently sequential). It also becomes significant for
6515  ! small-scale problems (N<100).
6516  !
6517  ! In such cases we strongly recommend you to use faster solver,
6518  ! HPDMatrixSolveMFast() function.
6519 
6520  ! COMMERCIAL EDITION OF ALGLIB:
6521  !
6522  ! Commercial Edition of ALGLIB includes following important improvements
6523  ! of this function:
6524  ! * high-performance native backend with same C# interface (C# version)
6525  ! * multithreading support (C++ and C# versions)
6526  ! * hardware vendor (Intel) implementations of linear algebra primitives
6527  ! (C++ and C# versions, x86/x64 platform)
6528  !
6529  ! We recommend you to read 'Working with commercial version' section of
6530  ! ALGLIB Reference Manual in order to find out how to use performance-
6531  ! related features provided by commercial edition of ALGLIB.
6532 
6533  INPUT PARAMETERS
6534  A - array[0..N-1,0..N-1], system matrix
6535  N - size of A
6536  IsUpper - what half of A is provided
6537  B - array[0..N-1,0..M-1], right part
6538  M - right part size
6539 
6540  OUTPUT PARAMETERS
6541  Info - same as in RMatrixSolve.
6542  Returns -3 for non-HPD matrices.
6543  Rep - same as in RMatrixSolve
6544  X - same as in RMatrixSolve
6545 
6546  -- ALGLIB --
6547  Copyright 27.01.2010 by Bochkanov Sergey
6548  *************************************************************************/
6549  public static void hpdmatrixsolvem(complex[,] a,
6550  int n,
6551  bool isupper,
6552  complex[,] b,
6553  int m,
6554  ref int info,
6555  densesolverreport rep,
6556  ref complex[,] x,
6557  alglib.xparams _params)
6558  {
6559  complex[,] da = new complex[0,0];
6560  int i = 0;
6561  int j = 0;
6562  int j1 = 0;
6563  int j2 = 0;
6564  int i_ = 0;
6565 
6566  info = 0;
6567  x = new complex[0,0];
6568 
6569 
6570  //
6571  // prepare: check inputs, allocate space...
6572  //
6573  if( n<=0 || m<=0 )
6574  {
6575  info = -1;
6576  return;
6577  }
6578  da = new complex[n, n];
6579 
6580  //
6581  // factorize matrix, solve
6582  //
6583  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
6584  {
6585  if( isupper )
6586  {
6587  j1 = i;
6588  j2 = n-1;
6589  }
6590  else
6591  {
6592  j1 = 0;
6593  j2 = i;
6594  }
6595  for(i_=j1; i_<=j2;i_++)
6596  {
6597  da[i,i_] = a[i,i_];
6598  }
6599  }
6600  if( !trfac.hpdmatrixcholesky(ref da, n, isupper, _params) )
6601  {
6602  x = new complex[n, m];
6603  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
6604  {
6605  for(j=0; j<=m-1; j++)
6606  {
6607  x[i,j] = 0;
6608  }
6609  }
6610  rep.r1 = 0;
6611  rep.rinf = 0;
6612  info = -3;
6613  return;
6614  }
6615  info = 1;
6616  hpdmatrixcholeskysolveinternal(da, n, isupper, a, true, b, m, ref info, rep, ref x, _params);
6617  }
6618

6620  /*************************************************************************
6621  Dense solver for A*X=B, with N*N Hermitian positive definite matrix A and
6622  N*M complex matrices X and B. "Fast-but-lightweight" version of the solver.
6623 
6624  Algorithm features:
6625  * O(N^3+M*N^2) complexity
6626  * matrix is represented by its upper or lower triangle
6627  * no additional time consuming features like condition number estimation
6628 
6629  ! COMMERCIAL EDITION OF ALGLIB:
6630  !
6631  ! Commercial Edition of ALGLIB includes following important improvements
6632  ! of this function:

6634  ! * multithreading support (C++ and C# versions)
6635  ! * hardware vendor (Intel) implementations of linear algebra primitives
6636  ! (C++ and C# versions, x86/x64 platform)

6640  ! related features provided by commercial edition of ALGLIB.
6641

6643  A - array[0..N-1,0..N-1], system matrix
6644  N - size of A

6647  M - right part size

6664  bool isupper,
6665  complex[,] b,
6666  int m,

6668  alglib.xparams _params)
6669  {

6671  int j = 0;
6672

6674  info = 0;
6675 
6676  info = 1;
6677  if( n<=0 )
6678  {
6679  info = -1;
6680  return;
6681  }
6682  if( !trfac.hpdmatrixcholesky(ref a, n, isupper, _params) )
6683  {
6684  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
6685  {

6687  {
6688  b[i,j] = 0.0;
6689  }
6690  }

6698  }
6699  else
6700  {
6701  ablas.cmatrixlefttrsm(n, m, a, 0, 0, false, false, 0, b, 0, 0, _params);
6702  ablas.cmatrixlefttrsm(n, m, a, 0, 0, false, false, 2, b, 0, 0, _params);

6875  /*************************************************************************
6876  Dense solver for A*X=B with N*N Hermitian positive definite matrix A given
6877  by its Cholesky decomposition and N*M complex matrices X and B. This is
6878  "slow-but-feature-rich" version of the solver which, in addition to the
6879  solution, estimates condition number of the system.
6880 
6881  Algorithm features:
6882  * automatic detection of degenerate cases
6883  * O(M*N^2) complexity
6884  * condition number estimation
6885  * matrix is represented by its upper or lower triangle
6886 
6887  No iterative refinement is provided because such partial representation of
6888  matrix does not allow efficient calculation of extra-precise matrix-vector
6889  products for large matrices. Use RMatrixSolve or RMatrixMixedSolve if you
6890  need iterative refinement.
6891 
6892  IMPORTANT: ! this function is NOT the most efficient linear solver provided
6893  ! by ALGLIB. It estimates condition number of linear system,
6894  ! which results in significant performance penalty when
6895  ! compared with "fast" version which just calls triangular
6896  ! solver. Amount of overhead introduced depends on M (the
6897  ! larger - the more efficient).
6898  !
6899  ! This performance penalty is insignificant when compared with
6900  ! cost of large Cholesky decomposition. However, if you call
6901  ! this function many times for the same left side, this
6902  ! overhead BECOMES significant. It also becomes significant
6903  ! for small-scale problems (N<50).
6904  !
6905  ! In such cases we strongly recommend you to use faster solver,
6906  ! HPDMatrixCholeskySolveMFast() function.

6910  CHA - array[N,N], Cholesky decomposition,
6911  HPDMatrixCholesky result
6912  N - size of CHA
6913  IsUpper - what half of CHA is provided
6914  B - array[N,M], right part
6915  M - right part size
6916 
6917  OUTPUT PARAMETERS:
6918  Info - return code:
6919  * -3 A is singular, or VERY close to singular.
6920  X is filled by zeros in such cases.
6921  * -1 N<=0 was passed
6922  * 1 task was solved
6923  Rep - additional report, following fields are set:
6924  * rep.r1 condition number in 1-norm
6925  * rep.rinf condition number in inf-norm
6926  X - array[N]:
6927  * for info>0 contains solution
6928  * for info=-3 filled by zeros
6929 
6930  -- ALGLIB --
6931  Copyright 27.01.2010 by Bochkanov Sergey
6932  *************************************************************************/
6933  public static void hpdmatrixcholeskysolvem(complex[,] cha,
6934  int n,
6935  bool isupper,
6936  complex[,] b,
6937  int m,
6938  ref int info,
6939  densesolverreport rep,
6940  ref complex[,] x,
6941  alglib.xparams _params)
6942  {
6943  complex[,] emptya = new complex[0,0];
6944 
6945  info = 0;
6946  x = new complex[0,0];
6947 
6948 
6949  //
6950  // prepare: check inputs, allocate space...
6951  //
6952  if( n<=0 || m<=0 )
6953  {
6954  info = -1;
6955  return;
6956  }
6957 
6958  //
6959  // 1. scale matrix, max(|U[i,j]|)
6960  // 2. factorize scaled matrix
6961  // 3. solve
6962  //
6963  hpdmatrixcholeskysolveinternal(cha, n, isupper, emptya, false, b, m, ref info, rep, ref x, _params);

6967  /*************************************************************************
6968  Dense solver for A*X=B with N*N Hermitian positive definite matrix A given
6969  by its Cholesky decomposition and N*M complex matrices X and B. This is
6970  "fast-but-lightweight" version of the solver.

6972  Algorithm features:
6973  * O(M*N^2) complexity
6974  * matrix is represented by its upper or lower triangle
6975  * no additional time-consuming features
6976

6978  CHA - array[N,N], Cholesky decomposition,
6979  HPDMatrixCholesky result

6983  M - right part size
6984 
6985  OUTPUT PARAMETERS:
6986  Info - return code:
6987  * -3 A is singular, or VERY close to singular.
6988  X is filled by zeros in such cases.
6989  * -1 N<=0 was passed
6990  * 1 task was solved
6991  B - array[N]:
6992  * for info>0 overwritten by solution
6993  * for info=-3 filled by zeros
6994 
6995  -- ALGLIB --
6996  Copyright 18.03.2015 by Bochkanov Sergey
6997  *************************************************************************/
6998  public static void hpdmatrixcholeskysolvemfast(complex[,] cha,
6999  int n,
7000  bool isupper,
7001  complex[,] b,
7002  int m,
7003  ref int info,
7004  alglib.xparams _params)
7005  {
7006  int i = 0;
7007  int j = 0;
7008  int k = 0;
7009 
7010  info = 0;
7011 
7012  info = 1;
7013  if( n<=0 )
7014  {
7015  info = -1;
7016  return;
7017  }
7018  for(k=0; k<=n-1; k++)
7019  {
7020  if( (double)(cha[k,k].x)==(double)(0.0) && (double)(cha[k,k].y)==(double)(0.0) )
7021  {
7022  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
7023  {
7024  for(j=0; j<=m-1; j++)
7025  {
7026  b[i,j] = 0.0;
7027  }
7028  }
7029  info = -3;
7030  return;
7031  }
7032  }
7033  if( isupper )
7034  {
7035  ablas.cmatrixlefttrsm(n, m, cha, 0, 0, true, false, 2, b, 0, 0, _params);
7036  ablas.cmatrixlefttrsm(n, m, cha, 0, 0, true, false, 0, b, 0, 0, _params);
7037  }
7038  else
7039  {
7040  ablas.cmatrixlefttrsm(n, m, cha, 0, 0, false, false, 0, b, 0, 0, _params);
7041  ablas.cmatrixlefttrsm(n, m, cha, 0, 0, false, false, 2, b, 0, 0, _params);
7042  }
7043  }
7044 
7045 
7046  /*************************************************************************
7047  Dense solver for A*x=b with N*N Hermitian positive definite matrix A given
7048  by its Cholesky decomposition, and N*1 complex vectors x and b. This is
7049  "slow-but-feature-rich" version of the solver which estimates condition
7050  number of the system.
7051 
7052  Algorithm features:
7053  * automatic detection of degenerate cases
7054  * O(N^2) complexity
7055  * condition number estimation
7056  * matrix is represented by its upper or lower triangle
7057 
7058  No iterative refinement is provided because such partial representation of
7059  matrix does not allow efficient calculation of extra-precise matrix-vector
7060  products for large matrices. Use RMatrixSolve or RMatrixMixedSolve if you
7061  need iterative refinement.
7062 
7063  IMPORTANT: ! this function is NOT the most efficient linear solver provided
7064  ! by ALGLIB. It estimates condition number of linear system,
7065  ! which results in 10-15x performance penalty when compared
7066  ! with "fast" version which just calls triangular solver.
7067  !
7068  ! This performance penalty is insignificant when compared with
7069  ! cost of large LU decomposition. However, if you call this
7070  ! function many times for the same left side, this overhead
7071  ! BECOMES significant. It also becomes significant for small-
7072  ! scale problems (N<50).
7073  !
7074  ! In such cases we strongly recommend you to use faster solver,
7075  ! HPDMatrixCholeskySolveFast() function.
7076 
7077  INPUT PARAMETERS
7078  CHA - array[0..N-1,0..N-1], Cholesky decomposition,
7079  SPDMatrixCholesky result
7080  N - size of A
7081  IsUpper - what half of CHA is provided
7082  B - array[0..N-1], right part
7083 
7084  OUTPUT PARAMETERS
7085  Info - return code:
7086  * -3 A is is exactly singular or ill conditioned
7087  X is filled by zeros in such cases.
7088  * -1 N<=0 was passed
7089  * 1 task is solved
7090  Rep - additional report, following fields are set:
7091  * rep.r1 condition number in 1-norm
7092  * rep.rinf condition number in inf-norm
7093  X - array[N]:
7094  * for info>0 - solution
7095  * for info=-3 - filled by zeros
7096 
7097  -- ALGLIB --
7098  Copyright 27.01.2010 by Bochkanov Sergey
7099  *************************************************************************/
7100  public static void hpdmatrixcholeskysolve(complex[,] cha,
7101  int n,
7102  bool isupper,
7103  complex[] b,
7104  ref int info,
7105  densesolverreport rep,
7106  ref complex[] x,
7107  alglib.xparams _params)
7108  {
7109  complex[,] bm = new complex[0,0];
7110  complex[,] xm = new complex[0,0];
7111  int i_ = 0;
7112 
7113  info = 0;
7114  x = new complex[0];
7115 
7116  if( n<=0 )
7117  {
7118  info = -1;
7119  return;
7120  }
7121  bm = new complex[n, 1];
7122  for(i_=0; i_<=n-1;i_++)
7123  {
7124  bm[i_,0] = b[i_];
7125  }
7126  hpdmatrixcholeskysolvem(cha, n, isupper, bm, 1, ref info, rep, ref xm, _params);
7127  x = new complex[n];
7128  for(i_=0; i_<=n-1;i_++)
7129  {
7130  x[i_] = xm[i_,0];
7131  }
7132  }
7133 
7134 
7135  /*************************************************************************
7136  Dense solver for A*x=b with N*N Hermitian positive definite matrix A given
7137  by its Cholesky decomposition, and N*1 complex vectors x and b. This is
7138  "fast-but-lightweight" version of the solver.
7139 
7140  Algorithm features:
7141  * O(N^2) complexity
7142  * matrix is represented by its upper or lower triangle
7143  * no additional time-consuming features
7144 
7145  INPUT PARAMETERS
7146  CHA - array[0..N-1,0..N-1], Cholesky decomposition,
7147  SPDMatrixCholesky result
7148  N - size of A
7149  IsUpper - what half of CHA is provided
7150  B - array[0..N-1], right part
7151 
7152  OUTPUT PARAMETERS
7153  Info - return code:
7154  * -3 A is is exactly singular or ill conditioned
7155  B is filled by zeros in such cases.
7156  * -1 N<=0 was passed
7157  * 1 task is solved
7158  B - array[N]:
7159  * for info>0 - overwritten by solution
7160  * for info=-3 - filled by zeros
7161 
7162  -- ALGLIB --
7163  Copyright 18.03.2015 by Bochkanov Sergey
7164  *************************************************************************/
7165  public static void hpdmatrixcholeskysolvefast(complex[,] cha,
7166  int n,
7167  bool isupper,
7168  complex[] b,
7169  ref int info,
7170  alglib.xparams _params)
7171  {
7172  int i = 0;
7173  int k = 0;
7174 
7175  info = 0;
7176 
7177  info = 1;
7178  if( n<=0 )
7179  {
7180  info = -1;
7181  return;
7182  }
7183  for(k=0; k<=n-1; k++)
7184  {
7185  if( (double)(cha[k,k].x)==(double)(0.0) && (double)(cha[k,k].y)==(double)(0.0) )
7186  {
7187  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
7188  {
7189  b[i] = 0.0;
7190  }
7191  info = -3;
7192  return;
7193  }
7194  }
7195  hpdbasiccholeskysolve(cha, n, isupper, b, _params);
7196  }
7197 
7198 
7199  /*************************************************************************
7200  Dense solver.
7201 
7202  This subroutine finds solution of the linear system A*X=B with non-square,
7203  possibly degenerate A. System is solved in the least squares sense, and
7204  general least squares solution X = X0 + CX*y which minimizes |A*X-B| is
7205  returned. If A is non-degenerate, solution in the usual sense is returned.
7206 
7207  Algorithm features:
7208  * automatic detection (and correct handling!) of degenerate cases
7209  * iterative refinement
7210  * O(N^3) complexity
7211 
7212  ! COMMERCIAL EDITION OF ALGLIB:
7213  !
7214  ! Commercial Edition of ALGLIB includes following important improvements
7215  ! of this function:
7216  ! * high-performance native backend with same C# interface (C# version)
7217  ! * multithreading support (C++ and C# versions)
7218  ! * hardware vendor (Intel) implementations of linear algebra primitives
7219  ! (C++ and C# versions, x86/x64 platform)
7220  !
7221  ! We recommend you to read 'Working with commercial version' section of
7222  ! ALGLIB Reference Manual in order to find out how to use performance-
7223  ! related features provided by commercial edition of ALGLIB.
7224 
7225  INPUT PARAMETERS
7226  A - array[0..NRows-1,0..NCols-1], system matrix
7227  NRows - vertical size of A
7228  NCols - horizontal size of A
7229  B - array[0..NCols-1], right part
7230  Threshold- a number in [0,1]. Singular values beyond Threshold are
7231  considered zero. Set it to 0.0, if you don't understand
7232  what it means, so the solver will choose good value on its
7233  own.
7234 
7235  OUTPUT PARAMETERS
7236  Info - return code:
7237  * -4 SVD subroutine failed
7238  * -1 if NRows<=0 or NCols<=0 or Threshold<0 was passed
7239  * 1 if task is solved
7240  Rep - solver report, see below for more info
7241  X - array[0..N-1,0..M-1], it contains:
7242  * solution of A*X=B (even for singular A)
7243  * zeros, if SVD subroutine failed
7244 
7245  SOLVER REPORT
7246 
7247  Subroutine sets following fields of the Rep structure:
7248  * R2 reciprocal of condition number: 1/cond(A), 2-norm.
7249  * N = NCols
7250  * K dim(Null(A))
7251  * CX array[0..N-1,0..K-1], kernel of A.
7252  Columns of CX store such vectors that A*CX[i]=0.
7253 
7254  -- ALGLIB --
7255  Copyright 24.08.2009 by Bochkanov Sergey
7256  *************************************************************************/
7257  public static void rmatrixsolvels(double[,] a,
7258  int nrows,
7259  int ncols,
7260  double[] b,
7261  double threshold,
7262  ref int info,
7263  densesolverlsreport rep,
7264  ref double[] x,
7265  alglib.xparams _params)
7266  {
7267  double[] sv = new double[0];
7268  double[,] u = new double[0,0];
7269  double[,] vt = new double[0,0];
7270  double[] rp = new double[0];
7271  double[] utb = new double[0];
7272  double[] sutb = new double[0];
7273  double[] tmp = new double[0];
7274  double[] ta = new double[0];
7275  double[] tx = new double[0];
7276  double[] buf = new double[0];
7277  double[] w = new double[0];
7278  int i = 0;
7279  int j = 0;
7280  int nsv = 0;
7281  int kernelidx = 0;
7282  double v = 0;
7283  double verr = 0;
7284  bool svdfailed = new bool();
7285  bool zeroa = new bool();
7286  int rfs = 0;
7287  int nrfs = 0;
7288  bool terminatenexttime = new bool();
7289  bool smallerr = new bool();
7290  int i_ = 0;
7291 
7292  info = 0;
7293  x = new double[0];
7294 
7295  if( (nrows<=0 || ncols<=0) || (double)(threshold)<(double)(0) )
7296  {
7297  info = -1;
7298  return;
7299  }
7300  if( (double)(threshold)==(double)(0) )
7301  {
7302  threshold = 1000*math.machineepsilon;
7303  }
7304 
7305  //
7306  // Factorize A first
7307  //
7308  svdfailed = !svd.rmatrixsvd(a, nrows, ncols, 1, 2, 2, ref sv, ref u, ref vt, _params);
7309  zeroa = (double)(sv[0])==(double)(0);
7310  if( svdfailed || zeroa )
7311  {
7312  if( svdfailed )
7313  {
7314  info = -4;
7315  }
7316  else
7317  {
7318  info = 1;
7319  }
7320  x = new double[ncols];
7321  for(i=0; i<=ncols-1; i++)
7322  {
7323  x[i] = 0;
7324  }
7325  rep.n = ncols;
7326  rep.k = ncols;
7327  rep.cx = new double[ncols, ncols];
7328  for(i=0; i<=ncols-1; i++)
7329  {
7330  for(j=0; j<=ncols-1; j++)
7331  {
7332  if( i==j )
7333  {
7334  rep.cx[i,j] = 1;
7335  }
7336  else
7337  {
7338  rep.cx[i,j] = 0;
7339  }
7340  }
7341  }
7342  rep.r2 = 0;
7343  return;
7344  }
7345  nsv = Math.Min(ncols, nrows);
7346  if( nsv==ncols )
7347  {
7348  rep.r2 = sv[nsv-1]/sv[0];
7349  }
7350  else
7351  {
7352  rep.r2 = 0;
7353  }
7354  rep.n = ncols;
7355  info = 1;
7356 
7357  //
7358  // Iterative refinement of xc combined with solution:
7359  // 1. xc = 0
7360  // 2. calculate r = bc-A*xc using extra-precise dot product
7361  // 3. solve A*y = r
7362  // 4. update x:=x+r
7363  // 5. goto 2
7364  //
7365  // This cycle is executed until one of two things happens:
7366  // 1. maximum number of iterations reached
7367  // 2. last iteration decreased error to the lower limit
7368  //
7369  utb = new double[nsv];
7370  sutb = new double[nsv];
7371  x = new double[ncols];
7372  tmp = new double[ncols];
7373  ta = new double[ncols+1];
7374  tx = new double[ncols+1];
7375  buf = new double[ncols+1];
7376  for(i=0; i<=ncols-1; i++)
7377  {
7378  x[i] = 0;
7379  }
7380  kernelidx = nsv;
7381  for(i=0; i<=nsv-1; i++)
7382  {
7383  if( (double)(sv[i])<=(double)(threshold*sv[0]) )
7384  {
7385  kernelidx = i;
7386  break;
7387  }
7388  }
7389  rep.k = ncols-kernelidx;
7390  nrfs = densesolverrfsmaxv2(ncols, rep.r2, _params);
7391  terminatenexttime = false;
7392  rp = new double[nrows];
7393  for(rfs=0; rfs<=nrfs; rfs++)
7394  {
7395  if( terminatenexttime )
7396  {
7397  break;
7398  }
7399 
7400  //
7401  // calculate right part
7402  //
7403  if( rfs==0 )
7404  {
7405  for(i_=0; i_<=nrows-1;i_++)
7406  {
7407  rp[i_] = b[i_];
7408  }
7409  }
7410  else
7411  {
7412  smallerr = true;
7413  for(i=0; i<=nrows-1; i++)
7414  {
7415  for(i_=0; i_<=ncols-1;i_++)
7416  {
7417  ta[i_] = a[i,i_];
7418  }
7419  ta[ncols] = -1;
7420  for(i_=0; i_<=ncols-1;i_++)
7421  {
7422  tx[i_] = x[i_];
7423  }
7424  tx[ncols] = b[i];
7425  xblas.xdot(ta, tx, ncols+1, ref buf, ref v, ref verr, _params);
7426  rp[i] = -v;
7427  smallerr = smallerr && (double)(Math.Abs(v))<(double)(4*verr);
7428  }
7429  if( smallerr )
7430  {
7431  terminatenexttime = true;
7432  }
7433  }
7434 
7435  //
7436  // solve A*dx = rp
7437  //
7438  for(i=0; i<=ncols-1; i++)
7439  {
7440  tmp[i] = 0;
7441  }
7442  for(i=0; i<=nsv-1; i++)
7443  {
7444  utb[i] = 0;
7445  }
7446  for(i=0; i<=nrows-1; i++)
7447  {
7448  v = rp[i];
7449  for(i_=0; i_<=nsv-1;i_++)
7450  {
7451  utb[i_] = utb[i_] + v*u[i,i_];
7452  }
7453  }
7454  for(i=0; i<=nsv-1; i++)
7455  {
7456  if( i<kernelidx )
7457  {
7458  sutb[i] = utb[i]/sv[i];
7459  }
7460  else
7461  {
7462  sutb[i] = 0;
7463  }
7464  }
7465  for(i=0; i<=nsv-1; i++)
7466  {
7467  v = sutb[i];
7468  for(i_=0; i_<=ncols-1;i_++)
7469  {
7470  tmp[i_] = tmp[i_] + v*vt[i,i_];
7471  }
7472  }
7473 
7474  //
7475  // update x: x:=x+dx
7476  //
7477  for(i_=0; i_<=ncols-1;i_++)
7478  {
7479  x[i_] = x[i_] + tmp[i_];
7480  }
7481  }
7482 
7483  //
7484  // fill CX
7485  //
7486  if( rep.k>0 )
7487  {
7488  rep.cx = new double[ncols, rep.k];
7489  for(i=0; i<=rep.k-1; i++)
7490  {
7491  for(i_=0; i_<=ncols-1;i_++)
7492  {
7493  rep.cx[i_,i] = vt[kernelidx+i,i_];
7494  }
7495  }
7496  }
7497  }
7498 
7499 
7500  /*************************************************************************
7501  Internal LU solver
7502 
7503  -- ALGLIB --
7504  Copyright 27.01.2010 by Bochkanov Sergey
7505  *************************************************************************/
7506  private static void rmatrixlusolveinternal(double[,] lua,
7507  int[] p,
7508  int n,
7509  double[,] a,
7510  bool havea,
7511  double[,] b,
7512  int m,
7513  ref int info,
7514  densesolverreport rep,
7515  ref double[,] x,
7516  alglib.xparams _params)
7517  {
7518  int i = 0;
7519  int j = 0;
7520  int k = 0;
7521  int rfs = 0;
7522  int nrfs = 0;
7523  double[] xc = new double[0];
7524  double[] y = new double[0];
7525  double[] bc = new double[0];
7526  double[] xa = new double[0];
7527  double[] xb = new double[0];
7528  double[] tx = new double[0];
7529  double v = 0;
7530  double verr = 0;
7531  double mxb = 0;
7532  bool smallerr = new bool();
7533  bool terminatenexttime = new bool();
7534  int i_ = 0;
7535 
7536  info = 0;
7537  x = new double[0,0];
7538 
7539 
7540  //
7541  // prepare: check inputs, allocate space...
7542  //
7543  if( n<=0 || m<=0 )
7544  {
7545  info = -1;
7546  return;
7547  }
7548  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
7549  {
7550  if( p[i]>n-1 || p[i]<i )
7551  {
7552  info = -1;
7553  return;
7554  }
7555  }
7556  x = new double[n, m];
7557  y = new double[n];
7558  xc = new double[n];
7559  bc = new double[n];
7560  tx = new double[n+1];
7561  xa = new double[n+1];
7562  xb = new double[n+1];
7563 
7564  //
7565  // estimate condition number, test for near singularity
7566  //
7567  rep.r1 = rcond.rmatrixlurcond1(lua, n, _params);
7568  rep.rinf = rcond.rmatrixlurcondinf(lua, n, _params);
7569  if( (double)(rep.r1)<(double)(rcond.rcondthreshold(_params)) || (double)(rep.rinf)<(double)(rcond.rcondthreshold(_params)) )
7570  {
7571  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
7572  {
7573  for(j=0; j<=m-1; j++)
7574  {
7575  x[i,j] = 0;
7576  }
7577  }
7578  rep.r1 = 0;
7579  rep.rinf = 0;
7580  info = -3;
7581  return;
7582  }
7583  info = 1;
7584 
7585  //
7586  // First stage of solution: rough solution with TRSM()
7587  //
7588  mxb = 0.0;
7589  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
7590  {
7591  for(j=0; j<=m-1; j++)
7592  {
7593  v = b[i,j];
7594  mxb = Math.Max(mxb, Math.Abs(v));
7595  x[i,j] = v;
7596  }
7597  }
7598  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
7599  {
7600  if( p[i]!=i )
7601  {
7602  for(j=0; j<=m-1; j++)
7603  {
7604  v = x[i,j];
7605  x[i,j] = x[p[i],j];
7606  x[p[i],j] = v;
7607  }
7608  }
7609  }
7610  ablas.rmatrixlefttrsm(n, m, lua, 0, 0, false, true, 0, x, 0, 0, _params);
7611  ablas.rmatrixlefttrsm(n, m, lua, 0, 0, true, false, 0, x, 0, 0, _params);
7612 
7613  //
7614  // Second stage: iterative refinement
7615  //
7616  if( havea )
7617  {
7618  for(k=0; k<=m-1; k++)
7619  {
7620  nrfs = densesolverrfsmax(n, rep.r1, rep.rinf, _params);
7621  terminatenexttime = false;
7622  for(rfs=0; rfs<=nrfs-1; rfs++)
7623  {
7624  if( terminatenexttime )
7625  {
7626  break;
7627  }
7628 
7629  //
7630  // generate right part
7631  //
7632  smallerr = true;
7633  for(i_=0; i_<=n-1;i_++)
7634  {
7635  xb[i_] = x[i_,k];
7636  }
7637  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
7638  {
7639  for(i_=0; i_<=n-1;i_++)
7640  {
7641  xa[i_] = a[i,i_];
7642  }
7643  xa[n] = -1;
7644  xb[n] = b[i,k];
7645  xblas.xdot(xa, xb, n+1, ref tx, ref v, ref verr, _params);
7646  y[i] = -v;
7647  smallerr = smallerr && (double)(Math.Abs(v))<(double)(4*verr);
7648  }
7649  if( smallerr )
7650  {
7651  terminatenexttime = true;
7652  }
7653 
7654  //
7655  // solve and update
7656  //
7657  rbasiclusolve(lua, p, n, y, _params);
7658  for(i_=0; i_<=n-1;i_++)
7659  {
7660  x[i_,k] = x[i_,k] + y[i_];
7661  }
7662  }
7663  }
7664  }
7665  }
7666 
7667 
7668  /*************************************************************************
7669  Internal Cholesky solver
7670 
7671  -- ALGLIB --
7672  Copyright 27.01.2010 by Bochkanov Sergey
7673  *************************************************************************/
7674  private static void spdmatrixcholeskysolveinternal(double[,] cha,
7675  int n,
7676  bool isupper,
7677  double[,] a,
7678  bool havea,
7679  double[,] b,
7680  int m,
7681  ref int info,
7682  densesolverreport rep,
7683  ref double[,] x,
7684  alglib.xparams _params)
7685  {
7686  int i = 0;
7687  int j = 0;
7688 
7689  info = 0;
7690  x = new double[0,0];
7691 
7692 
7693  //
7694  // prepare: check inputs, allocate space...
7695  //
7696  if( n<=0 || m<=0 )
7697  {
7698  info = -1;
7699  return;
7700  }
7701  x = new double[n, m];
7702 
7703  //
7704  // estimate condition number, test for near singularity
7705  //
7706  rep.r1 = rcond.spdmatrixcholeskyrcond(cha, n, isupper, _params);
7707  rep.rinf = rep.r1;
7708  if( (double)(rep.r1)<(double)(rcond.rcondthreshold(_params)) )
7709  {
7710  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
7711  {
7712  for(j=0; j<=m-1; j++)
7713  {
7714  x[i,j] = 0;
7715  }
7716  }
7717  rep.r1 = 0;
7718  rep.rinf = 0;
7719  info = -3;
7720  return;
7721  }
7722  info = 1;
7723 
7724  //
7725  // Solve with TRSM()
7726  //
7727  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
7728  {
7729  for(j=0; j<=m-1; j++)
7730  {
7731  x[i,j] = b[i,j];
7732  }
7733  }
7734  if( isupper )
7735  {
7736  ablas.rmatrixlefttrsm(n, m, cha, 0, 0, true, false, 1, x, 0, 0, _params);
7737  ablas.rmatrixlefttrsm(n, m, cha, 0, 0, true, false, 0, x, 0, 0, _params);
7738  }
7739  else
7740  {
7741  ablas.rmatrixlefttrsm(n, m, cha, 0, 0, false, false, 0, x, 0, 0, _params);
7742  ablas.rmatrixlefttrsm(n, m, cha, 0, 0, false, false, 1, x, 0, 0, _params);
7743  }
7744  }
7745 
7746 
7747  /*************************************************************************
7748  Internal LU solver
7749 
7750  -- ALGLIB --
7751  Copyright 27.01.2010 by Bochkanov Sergey
7752  *************************************************************************/
7753  private static void cmatrixlusolveinternal(complex[,] lua,
7754  int[] p,
7755  int n,
7756  complex[,] a,
7757  bool havea,
7758  complex[,] b,
7759  int m,
7760  ref int info,
7761  densesolverreport rep,
7762  ref complex[,] x,
7763  alglib.xparams _params)
7764  {
7765  int i = 0;
7766  int j = 0;
7767  int k = 0;
7768  int rfs = 0;
7769  int nrfs = 0;
7770  complex[] xc = new complex[0];
7771  complex[] y = new complex[0];
7772  complex[] bc = new complex[0];
7773  complex[] xa = new complex[0];
7774  complex[] xb = new complex[0];
7775  complex[] tx = new complex[0];
7776  double[] tmpbuf = new double[0];
7777  complex v = 0;
7778  double verr = 0;
7779  bool smallerr = new bool();
7780  bool terminatenexttime = new bool();
7781  int i_ = 0;
7782 
7783  info = 0;
7784  x = new complex[0,0];
7785 
7786 
7787  //
7788  // prepare: check inputs, allocate space...
7789  //
7790  if( n<=0 || m<=0 )
7791  {
7792  info = -1;
7793  return;
7794  }
7795  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
7796  {
7797  if( p[i]>n-1 || p[i]<i )
7798  {
7799  info = -1;
7800  return;
7801  }
7802  }
7803  x = new complex[n, m];
7804  y = new complex[n];
7805  xc = new complex[n];
7806  bc = new complex[n];
7807  tx = new complex[n];
7808  xa = new complex[n+1];
7809  xb = new complex[n+1];
7810  tmpbuf = new double[2*n+2];
7811 
7812  //
7813  // estimate condition number, test for near singularity
7814  //
7815  rep.r1 = rcond.cmatrixlurcond1(lua, n, _params);
7816  rep.rinf = rcond.cmatrixlurcondinf(lua, n, _params);
7817  if( (double)(rep.r1)<(double)(rcond.rcondthreshold(_params)) || (double)(rep.rinf)<(double)(rcond.rcondthreshold(_params)) )
7818  {
7819  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
7820  {
7821  for(j=0; j<=m-1; j++)
7822  {
7823  x[i,j] = 0;
7824  }
7825  }
7826  rep.r1 = 0;
7827  rep.rinf = 0;
7828  info = -3;
7829  return;
7830  }
7831  info = 1;
7832 
7833  //
7834  // First phase: solve with TRSM()
7835  //
7836  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
7837  {
7838  for(j=0; j<=m-1; j++)
7839  {
7840  x[i,j] = b[i,j];
7841  }
7842  }
7843  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
7844  {
7845  if( p[i]!=i )
7846  {
7847  for(j=0; j<=m-1; j++)
7848  {
7849  v = x[i,j];
7850  x[i,j] = x[p[i],j];
7851  x[p[i],j] = v;
7852  }
7853  }
7854  }
7855  ablas.cmatrixlefttrsm(n, m, lua, 0, 0, false, true, 0, x, 0, 0, _params);
7856  ablas.cmatrixlefttrsm(n, m, lua, 0, 0, true, false, 0, x, 0, 0, _params);
7857 
7858  //
7859  // solve
7860  //
7861  for(k=0; k<=m-1; k++)
7862  {
7863  for(i_=0; i_<=n-1;i_++)
7864  {
7865  bc[i_] = b[i_,k];
7866  }
7867  for(i_=0; i_<=n-1;i_++)
7868  {
7869  xc[i_] = x[i_,k];
7870  }
7871 
7872  //
7873  // Iterative refinement of xc:
7874  // * calculate r = bc-A*xc using extra-precise dot product
7875  // * solve A*y = r
7876  // * update x:=x+r
7877  //
7878  // This cycle is executed until one of two things happens:
7879  // 1. maximum number of iterations reached
7880  // 2. last iteration decreased error to the lower limit
7881  //
7882  if( havea )
7883  {
7884  nrfs = densesolverrfsmax(n, rep.r1, rep.rinf, _params);
7885  terminatenexttime = false;
7886  for(rfs=0; rfs<=nrfs-1; rfs++)
7887  {
7888  if( terminatenexttime )
7889  {
7890  break;
7891  }
7892 
7893  //
7894  // generate right part
7895  //
7896  smallerr = true;
7897  for(i_=0; i_<=n-1;i_++)
7898  {
7899  xb[i_] = xc[i_];
7900  }
7901  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
7902  {
7903  for(i_=0; i_<=n-1;i_++)
7904  {
7905  xa[i_] = a[i,i_];
7906  }
7907  xa[n] = -1;
7908  xb[n] = bc[i];
7909  xblas.xcdot(xa, xb, n+1, ref tmpbuf, ref v, ref verr, _params);
7910  y[i] = -v;
7911  smallerr = smallerr && (double)(math.abscomplex(v))<(double)(4*verr);
7912  }
7913  if( smallerr )
7914  {
7915  terminatenexttime = true;
7916  }
7917 
7918  //
7919  // solve and update
7920  //
7921  cbasiclusolve(lua, p, n, y, _params);
7922  for(i_=0; i_<=n-1;i_++)
7923  {
7924  xc[i_] = xc[i_] + y[i_];
7925  }
7926  }
7927  }
7928 
7929  //
7930  // Store xc.
7931  // Post-scale result.
7932  //
7933  for(i_=0; i_<=n-1;i_++)
7934  {
7935  x[i_,k] = xc[i_];
7936  }
7937  }
7938  }
7939 
7940 
7941  /*************************************************************************
7942  Internal Cholesky solver
7943 
7944  -- ALGLIB --
7945  Copyright 27.01.2010 by Bochkanov Sergey
7946  *************************************************************************/
7947  private static void hpdmatrixcholeskysolveinternal(complex[,] cha,
7948  int n,
7949  bool isupper,
7950  complex[,] a,
7951  bool havea,
7952  complex[,] b,
7953  int m,
7954  ref int info,
7955  densesolverreport rep,
7956  ref complex[,] x,
7957  alglib.xparams _params)
7958  {
7959  int i = 0;
7960  int j = 0;
7961  complex[] xc = new complex[0];
7962  complex[] y = new complex[0];
7963  complex[] bc = new complex[0];
7964  complex[] xa = new complex[0];
7965  complex[] xb = new complex[0];
7966  complex[] tx = new complex[0];
7967 
7968  info = 0;
7969  x = new complex[0,0];
7970 
7971 
7972  //
7973  // prepare: check inputs, allocate space...
7974  //
7975  if( n<=0 || m<=0 )
7976  {
7977  info = -1;
7978  return;
7979  }
7980  x = new complex[n, m];
7981  y = new complex[n];
7982  xc = new complex[n];
7983  bc = new complex[n];
7984  tx = new complex[n+1];
7985  xa = new complex[n+1];
7986  xb = new complex[n+1];
7987 
7988  //
7989  // estimate condition number, test for near singularity
7990  //
7991  rep.r1 = rcond.hpdmatrixcholeskyrcond(cha, n, isupper, _params);
7992  rep.rinf = rep.r1;
7993  if( (double)(rep.r1)<(double)(rcond.rcondthreshold(_params)) )
7994  {
7995  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
7996  {
7997  for(j=0; j<=m-1; j++)
7998  {
7999  x[i,j] = 0;
8000  }
8001  }
8002  rep.r1 = 0;
8003  rep.rinf = 0;
8004  info = -3;
8005  return;
8006  }
8007  info = 1;
8008 
8009  //
8010  // solve
8011  //
8012  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
8013  {
8014  for(j=0; j<=m-1; j++)
8015  {
8016  x[i,j] = b[i,j];
8017  }
8018  }
8019  if( isupper )
8020  {
8021  ablas.cmatrixlefttrsm(n, m, cha, 0, 0, true, false, 2, x, 0, 0, _params);
8022  ablas.cmatrixlefttrsm(n, m, cha, 0, 0, true, false, 0, x, 0, 0, _params);
8023  }
8024  else
8025  {
8026  ablas.cmatrixlefttrsm(n, m, cha, 0, 0, false, false, 0, x, 0, 0, _params);
8027  ablas.cmatrixlefttrsm(n, m, cha, 0, 0, false, false, 2, x, 0, 0, _params);
8028  }
8029  }
8030 
8031 
8032  /*************************************************************************
8033  Internal subroutine.
8034  Returns maximum count of RFS iterations as function of:
8035  1. machine epsilon
8036  2. task size.
8037  3. condition number
8038 
8039  -- ALGLIB --
8040  Copyright 27.01.2010 by Bochkanov Sergey
8041  *************************************************************************/
8042  private static int densesolverrfsmax(int n,
8043  double r1,
8044  double rinf,
8045  alglib.xparams _params)
8046  {
8047  int result = 0;
8048 
8049  result = 5;
8050  return result;
8051  }
8052 
8053 
8054  /*************************************************************************
8055  Internal subroutine.
8056  Returns maximum count of RFS iterations as function of:
8057  1. machine epsilon
8058  2. task size.
8059  3. norm-2 condition number
8060 
8061  -- ALGLIB --
8062  Copyright 27.01.2010 by Bochkanov Sergey
8063  *************************************************************************/
8064  private static int densesolverrfsmaxv2(int n,
8065  double r2,
8066  alglib.xparams _params)
8067  {
8068  int result = 0;
8069 
8070  result = densesolverrfsmax(n, 0, 0, _params);
8071  return result;
8072  }
8073 
8074 
8075  /*************************************************************************
8076  Basic LU solver for PLU*x = y.
8077 
8078  This subroutine assumes that:
8079  * A=PLU is well-conditioned, so no zero divisions or overflow may occur
8080 
8081  -- ALGLIB --
8082  Copyright 27.01.2010 by Bochkanov Sergey
8083  *************************************************************************/
8084  private static void rbasiclusolve(double[,] lua,
8085  int[] p,
8086  int n,
8087  double[] xb,
8088  alglib.xparams _params)
8089  {
8090  int i = 0;
8091  double v = 0;
8092  int i_ = 0;
8093 
8094  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
8095  {
8096  if( p[i]!=i )
8097  {
8098  v = xb[i];
8099  xb[i] = xb[p[i]];
8100  xb[p[i]] = v;
8101  }
8102  }
8103  for(i=1; i<=n-1; i++)
8104  {
8105  v = 0.0;
8106  for(i_=0; i_<=i-1;i_++)
8107  {
8108  v += lua[i,i_]*xb[i_];
8109  }
8110  xb[i] = xb[i]-v;
8111  }
8112  xb[n-1] = xb[n-1]/lua[n-1,n-1];
8113  for(i=n-2; i>=0; i--)
8114  {
8115  v = 0.0;
8116  for(i_=i+1; i_<=n-1;i_++)
8117  {
8118  v += lua[i,i_]*xb[i_];
8119  }
8120  xb[i] = (xb[i]-v)/lua[i,i];
8121  }
8122  }
8123 
8124 
8125  /*************************************************************************
8126  Basic Cholesky solver for ScaleA*Cholesky(A)'*x = y.
8127 
8128  This subroutine assumes that:
8129  * A*ScaleA is well scaled
8130  * A is well-conditioned, so no zero divisions or overflow may occur
8131 
8132  -- ALGLIB --
8133  Copyright 27.01.2010 by Bochkanov Sergey
8134  *************************************************************************/
8135  private static void spdbasiccholeskysolve(double[,] cha,
8136  int n,
8137  bool isupper,
8138  double[] xb,
8139  alglib.xparams _params)
8140  {
8141  int i = 0;
8142  double v = 0;
8143  int i_ = 0;
8144 
8145 
8146  //
8147  // A = L*L' or A=U'*U
8148  //
8149  if( isupper )
8150  {
8151 
8152  //
8153  // Solve U'*y=b first.
8154  //
8155  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
8156  {
8157  xb[i] = xb[i]/cha[i,i];
8158  if( i<n-1 )
8159  {
8160  v = xb[i];
8161  for(i_=i+1; i_<=n-1;i_++)
8162  {
8163  xb[i_] = xb[i_] - v*cha[i,i_];
8164  }
8165  }
8166  }
8167 
8168  //
8169  // Solve U*x=y then.
8170  //
8171  for(i=n-1; i>=0; i--)
8172  {
8173  if( i<n-1 )
8174  {
8175  v = 0.0;
8176  for(i_=i+1; i_<=n-1;i_++)
8177  {
8178  v += cha[i,i_]*xb[i_];
8179  }
8180  xb[i] = xb[i]-v;
8181  }
8182  xb[i] = xb[i]/cha[i,i];
8183  }
8184  }
8185  else
8186  {
8187 
8188  //
8189  // Solve L*y=b first
8190  //
8191  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
8192  {
8193  if( i>0 )
8194  {
8195  v = 0.0;
8196  for(i_=0; i_<=i-1;i_++)
8197  {
8198  v += cha[i,i_]*xb[i_];
8199  }
8200  xb[i] = xb[i]-v;
8201  }
8202  xb[i] = xb[i]/cha[i,i];
8203  }
8204 
8205  //
8206  // Solve L'*x=y then.
8207  //
8208  for(i=n-1; i>=0; i--)
8209  {
8210  xb[i] = xb[i]/cha[i,i];
8211  if( i>0 )
8212  {
8213  v = xb[i];
8214  for(i_=0; i_<=i-1;i_++)
8215  {
8216  xb[i_] = xb[i_] - v*cha[i,i_];
8217  }
8218  }
8219  }
8220  }
8221  }
8222 
8223 
8224  /*************************************************************************
8225  Basic LU solver for ScaleA*PLU*x = y.
8226 
8227  This subroutine assumes that:
8228  * L is well-scaled, and it is U which needs scaling by ScaleA.
8229  * A=PLU is well-conditioned, so no zero divisions or overflow may occur
8230 
8231  -- ALGLIB --
8232  Copyright 27.01.2010 by Bochkanov Sergey
8233  *************************************************************************/
8234  private static void cbasiclusolve(complex[,] lua,
8235  int[] p,
8236  int n,
8237  complex[] xb,
8238  alglib.xparams _params)
8239  {
8240  int i = 0;
8241  complex v = 0;
8242  int i_ = 0;
8243 
8244  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
8245  {
8246  if( p[i]!=i )
8247  {
8248  v = xb[i];
8249  xb[i] = xb[p[i]];
8250  xb[p[i]] = v;
8251  }
8252  }
8253  for(i=1; i<=n-1; i++)
8254  {
8255  v = 0.0;
8256  for(i_=0; i_<=i-1;i_++)
8257  {
8258  v += lua[i,i_]*xb[i_];
8259  }
8260  xb[i] = xb[i]-v;
8261  }
8262  xb[n-1] = xb[n-1]/lua[n-1,n-1];
8263  for(i=n-2; i>=0; i--)
8264  {
8265  v = 0.0;
8266  for(i_=i+1; i_<=n-1;i_++)
8267  {
8268  v += lua[i,i_]*xb[i_];
8269  }
8270  xb[i] = (xb[i]-v)/lua[i,i];
8271  }
8272  }
8273 
8274 
8275  /*************************************************************************
8276  Basic Cholesky solver for ScaleA*Cholesky(A)'*x = y.
8277 
8278  This subroutine assumes that:
8279  * A*ScaleA is well scaled
8280  * A is well-conditioned, so no zero divisions or overflow may occur
8281 
8282  -- ALGLIB --
8283  Copyright 27.01.2010 by Bochkanov Sergey
8284  *************************************************************************/
8285  private static void hpdbasiccholeskysolve(complex[,] cha,
8286  int n,
8287  bool isupper,
8288  complex[] xb,
8289  alglib.xparams _params)
8290  {
8291  int i = 0;
8292  complex v = 0;
8293  int i_ = 0;
8294 
8295 
8296  //
8297  // A = L*L' or A=U'*U
8298  //
8299  if( isupper )
8300  {
8301 
8302  //
8303  // Solve U'*y=b first.
8304  //
8305  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
8306  {
8307  xb[i] = xb[i]/math.conj(cha[i,i]);
8308  if( i<n-1 )
8309  {
8310  v = xb[i];
8311  for(i_=i+1; i_<=n-1;i_++)
8312  {
8313  xb[i_] = xb[i_] - v*math.conj(cha[i,i_]);
8314  }
8315  }
8316  }
8317 
8318  //
8319  // Solve U*x=y then.
8320  //
8321  for(i=n-1; i>=0; i--)
8322  {
8323  if( i<n-1 )
8324  {
8325  v = 0.0;
8326  for(i_=i+1; i_<=n-1;i_++)
8327  {
8328  v += cha[i,i_]*xb[i_];
8329  }
8330  xb[i] = xb[i]-v;
8331  }
8332  xb[i] = xb[i]/cha[i,i];
8333  }
8334  }
8335  else
8336  {
8337 
8338  //
8339  // Solve L*y=b first
8340  //
8341  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
8342  {
8343  if( i>0 )
8344  {
8345  v = 0.0;
8346  for(i_=0; i_<=i-1;i_++)
8347  {
8348  v += cha[i,i_]*xb[i_];
8349  }
8350  xb[i] = xb[i]-v;
8351  }
8352  xb[i] = xb[i]/cha[i,i];
8353  }
8354 
8355  //
8356  // Solve L'*x=y then.
8357  //
8358  for(i=n-1; i>=0; i--)
8359  {
8360  xb[i] = xb[i]/math.conj(cha[i,i]);
8361  if( i>0 )
8362  {
8363  v = xb[i];
8364  for(i_=0; i_<=i-1;i_++)
8365  {
8366  xb[i_] = xb[i_] - v*math.conj(cha[i,i_]);
8367  }
8368  }
8369  }
8370  }
8371  }
8372 
8373 
8374  }

8459  }
8460  public override alglib.apobject make_copy()
8461  {
8462  linlsqrstate _result = new linlsqrstate();
8463  _result.nes = (normestimator.normestimatorstate)nes.make_copy();
8464  _result.rx = (double[])rx.Clone();
8465  _result.b = (double[])b.Clone();
8466  _result.n = n;
8467  _result.m = m;
8468  _result.prectype = prectype;
8469  _result.ui = (double[])ui.Clone();
8470  _result.uip1 = (double[])uip1.Clone();
8471  _result.vi = (double[])vi.Clone();
8472  _result.vip1 = (double[])vip1.Clone();
8473  _result.omegai = (double[])omegai.Clone();
8474  _result.omegaip1 = (double[])omegaip1.Clone();
8475  _result.alphai = alphai;
8476  _result.alphaip1 = alphaip1;
8477  _result.betai = betai;
8478  _result.betaip1 = betaip1;
8479  _result.phibari = phibari;
8480  _result.phibarip1 = phibarip1;
8481  _result.phii = phii;
8482  _result.rhobari = rhobari;
8483  _result.rhobarip1 = rhobarip1;
8484  _result.rhoi = rhoi;
8485  _result.ci = ci;
8486  _result.si = si;
8487  _result.theta = theta;
8488  _result.lambdai = lambdai;
8489  _result.d = (double[])d.Clone();
8490  _result.anorm = anorm;
8491  _result.bnorm2 = bnorm2;
8492  _result.dnorm = dnorm;
8493  _result.r2 = r2;
8494  _result.x = (double[])x.Clone();
8495  _result.mv = (double[])mv.Clone();
8496  _result.mtv = (double[])mtv.Clone();
8497  _result.epsa = epsa;
8498  _result.epsb = epsb;
8499  _result.epsc = epsc;
8500  _result.maxits = maxits;
8501  _result.xrep = xrep;
8502  _result.xupdated = xupdated;
8503  _result.needmv = needmv;
8504  _result.needmtv = needmtv;
8505  _result.needmv2 = needmv2;
8506  _result.needvmv = needvmv;
8507  _result.needprec = needprec;
8508  _result.repiterationscount = repiterationscount;
8509  _result.repnmv = repnmv;
8510  _result.repterminationtype = repterminationtype;
8511  _result.running = running;
8512  _result.userterminationneeded = userterminationneeded;
8513  _result.tmpd = (double[])tmpd.Clone();
8514  _result.tmpx = (double[])tmpx.Clone();
8515  _result.rstate = (rcommstate)rstate.make_copy();
8516  return _result;
8517  }
8518  };

8525  public int terminationtype;

8527  {
8528  init();
8529  }
8530  public override void init()
8531  {
8532  }
8533  public override alglib.apobject make_copy()
8534  {
8535  linlsqrreport _result = new linlsqrreport();
8536  _result.iterationscount = iterationscount;
8537  _result.nmv = nmv;
8538  _result.terminationtype = terminationtype;
