11075 
11076  /*************************************************************************
11077  This function initializes linear CG Solver. This solver is used to solve
11078  symmetric positive definite problems. If you want to solve nonsymmetric
11079  (or non-positive definite) problem you may use LinLSQR solver provided by
11080  ALGLIB.
11081 
11082  USAGE:
11083  1. User initializes algorithm state with LinCGCreate() call
11084  2. User tunes solver parameters with LinCGSetCond() and other functions
11085  3. Optionally, user sets starting point with LinCGSetStartingPoint()
11086  4. User calls LinCGSolveSparse() function which takes algorithm state and
11087  SparseMatrix object.
11088  5. User calls LinCGResults() to get solution
11089  6. Optionally, user may call LinCGSolveSparse() again to solve another
11090  problem with different matrix and/or right part without reinitializing
11091  LinCGState structure.
11092 
11093  INPUT PARAMETERS:
11094  N - problem dimension, N>0
11095 
11096  OUTPUT PARAMETERS:
11097  State - structure which stores algorithm state
11098 
11099  -- ALGLIB --
11100  Copyright 14.11.2011 by Bochkanov Sergey
11101  *************************************************************************/
11102  public static void lincgcreate(int n,
11103  lincgstate state,
11104  alglib.xparams _params)
11105  {
11106  int i = 0;
11107 
11108  alglib.ap.assert(n>0, "LinCGCreate: N<=0");
11109  state.n = n;
11110  state.prectype = 0;
11111  state.itsbeforerestart = n;
11112  state.itsbeforerupdate = 10;
11113  state.epsf = defaultprecision;
11114  state.maxits = 0;
11115  state.xrep = false;
11116  state.running = false;
11117 
11118  //
11119  // * allocate arrays
11120  // * set RX to NAN (just for the case user calls Results() without
11121  // calling SolveSparse()
11122  // * set starting point to zero
11123  // * we do NOT initialize B here because we assume that user should
11124  // initializate it using LinCGSetB() function. In case he forgets
11125  // to do so, exception will be thrown in the LinCGIteration().
11126  //
11127  state.rx = new double[state.n];
11128  state.startx = new double[state.n];
11129  state.b = new double[state.n];
11130  for(i=0; i<=state.n-1; i++)
11131  {
11132  state.rx[i] = Double.NaN;
11133  state.startx[i] = 0.0;
11134  state.b[i] = 0;
11135  }
11136  state.cx = new double[state.n];
11137  state.p = new double[state.n];
11138  state.r = new double[state.n];
11139  state.cr = new double[state.n];
11140  state.z = new double[state.n];
11141  state.cz = new double[state.n];
11142  state.x = new double[state.n];
11143  state.mv = new double[state.n];
11144  state.pv = new double[state.n];
11145  updateitersdata(state, _params);
11146  state.rstate.ia = new int[0+1];
11147  state.rstate.ra = new double[2+1];
11148  state.rstate.stage = -1;
11149  }
11150 
11151 
11152  /*************************************************************************
11153  This function sets starting point.
11154  By default, zero starting point is used.
11155 
11156  INPUT PARAMETERS:
11157  X - starting point, array[N]
11158 
11159  OUTPUT PARAMETERS:
11160  State - structure which stores algorithm state
11161 
11162  -- ALGLIB --
11163  Copyright 14.11.2011 by Bochkanov Sergey
11164  *************************************************************************/
11165  public static void lincgsetstartingpoint(lincgstate state,
11166  double[] x,
11167  alglib.xparams _params)
11168  {
11169  int i_ = 0;
11170 
11171  alglib.ap.assert(!state.running, "LinCGSetStartingPoint: you can not change starting point because LinCGIteration() function is running");
11172  alglib.ap.assert(state.n<=alglib.ap.len(x), "LinCGSetStartingPoint: Length(X)<N");
11173  alglib.ap.assert(apserv.isfinitevector(x, state.n, _params), "LinCGSetStartingPoint: X contains infinite or NaN values!");
11174  for(i_=0; i_<=state.n-1;i_++)
11175  {
11176  state.startx[i_] = x[i_];
11177  }
11178  }
11179 
11180 
11181  /*************************************************************************
11182  This function sets right part. By default, right part is zero.
11183 
11184  INPUT PARAMETERS:
11185  B - right part, array[N].
11186 
11187  OUTPUT PARAMETERS:
11188  State - structure which stores algorithm state
11189 
11190  -- ALGLIB --
11191  Copyright 14.11.2011 by Bochkanov Sergey
11192  *************************************************************************/
11193  public static void lincgsetb(lincgstate state,
11194  double[] b,
11195  alglib.xparams _params)
11196  {
11197  int i_ = 0;
11198 
11199  alglib.ap.assert(!state.running, "LinCGSetB: you can not set B, because function LinCGIteration is running!");
11200  alglib.ap.assert(alglib.ap.len(b)>=state.n, "LinCGSetB: Length(B)<N");
11201  alglib.ap.assert(apserv.isfinitevector(b, state.n, _params), "LinCGSetB: B contains infinite or NaN values!");
11202  for(i_=0; i_<=state.n-1;i_++)
11203  {
11204  state.b[i_] = b[i_];
11205  }
11206  }
11207 
11208 
11209  /*************************************************************************
11210  This function changes preconditioning settings of LinCGSolveSparse()
11211  function. By default, SolveSparse() uses diagonal preconditioner, but if
11212  you want to use solver without preconditioning, you can call this function
11213  which forces solver to use unit matrix for preconditioning.
11214 
11215  INPUT PARAMETERS:
11216  State - structure which stores algorithm state
11217 
11218  -- ALGLIB --
11219  Copyright 19.11.2012 by Bochkanov Sergey
11220  *************************************************************************/
11221  public static void lincgsetprecunit(lincgstate state,
11222  alglib.xparams _params)
11223  {
11224  alglib.ap.assert(!state.running, "LinCGSetPrecUnit: you can not change preconditioner, because function LinCGIteration is running!");
11225  state.prectype = -1;
11226  }
11227 
11228 
11229  /*************************************************************************
11230  This function changes preconditioning settings of LinCGSolveSparse()
11231  function. LinCGSolveSparse() will use diagonal of the system matrix as
11232  preconditioner. This preconditioning mode is active by default.
11233 
11234  INPUT PARAMETERS:
11235  State - structure which stores algorithm state
11236 
11237  -- ALGLIB --
11238  Copyright 19.11.2012 by Bochkanov Sergey
11239  *************************************************************************/
11240  public static void lincgsetprecdiag(lincgstate state,
11241  alglib.xparams _params)
11242  {
11243  alglib.ap.assert(!state.running, "LinCGSetPrecDiag: you can not change preconditioner, because function LinCGIteration is running!");
11244  state.prectype = 0;
11245  }
11246 
11247 
11248  /*************************************************************************
11249  This function sets stopping criteria.
11250 
11251  INPUT PARAMETERS:
11252  EpsF - algorithm will be stopped if norm of residual is less than
11253  EpsF*||b||.
11254  MaxIts - algorithm will be stopped if number of iterations is more
11255  than MaxIts.
11256 
11257  OUTPUT PARAMETERS:
11258  State - structure which stores algorithm state
11259 
11260  NOTES:
11261  If both EpsF and MaxIts are zero then small EpsF will be set to small
11262  value.
11263 
11264  -- ALGLIB --
11265  Copyright 14.11.2011 by Bochkanov Sergey
11266  *************************************************************************/
11267  public static void lincgsetcond(lincgstate state,
11268  double epsf,
11269  int maxits,
11270  alglib.xparams _params)
11271  {
11272  alglib.ap.assert(!state.running, "LinCGSetCond: you can not change stopping criteria when LinCGIteration() is running");
11273  alglib.ap.assert(math.isfinite(epsf) && (double)(epsf)>=(double)(0), "LinCGSetCond: EpsF is negative or contains infinite or NaN values");
11274  alglib.ap.assert(maxits>=0, "LinCGSetCond: MaxIts is negative");
11275  if( (double)(epsf)==(double)(0) && maxits==0 )
11276  {
11277  state.epsf = defaultprecision;
11278  state.maxits = maxits;
11279  }
11280  else
11281  {
11282  state.epsf = epsf;
11283  state.maxits = maxits;
11284  }
11285  }
11286 
11287 
11288  /*************************************************************************
11289  Reverse communication version of linear CG.
11290 
11291  -- ALGLIB --
11292  Copyright 14.11.2011 by Bochkanov Sergey
11293  *************************************************************************/
11294  public static bool lincgiteration(lincgstate state,
11295  alglib.xparams _params)
11296  {
11297  bool result = new bool();
11298  int i = 0;
11299  double uvar = 0;
11300  double bnorm = 0;
11301  double v = 0;
11302  int i_ = 0;
11303 
11304 
11305  //
11306  // Reverse communication preparations
11307  // I know it looks ugly, but it works the same way
11308  // anywhere from C++ to Python.
11309  //
11310  // This code initializes locals by:
11311  // * random values determined during code
11312  // generation - on first subroutine call
11313  // * values from previous call - on subsequent calls
11314  //
11315  if( state.rstate.stage>=0 )
11316  {
11317  i = state.rstate.ia[0];
11318  uvar = state.rstate.ra[0];
11319  bnorm = state.rstate.ra[1];
11320  v = state.rstate.ra[2];
11321  }
11322  else
11323  {
11324  i = 359;
11325  uvar = -58;
11326  bnorm = -919;
11327  v = -909;
11328  }
11329  if( state.rstate.stage==0 )
11330  {
11331  goto lbl_0;
11332  }
11333  if( state.rstate.stage==1 )
11334  {
11335  goto lbl_1;
11336  }
11337  if( state.rstate.stage==2 )
11338  {
11339  goto lbl_2;
11340  }
11341  if( state.rstate.stage==3 )
11342  {
11343  goto lbl_3;
11344  }
11345  if( state.rstate.stage==4 )
11346  {
11347  goto lbl_4;
11348  }
11349  if( state.rstate.stage==5 )
11350  {
11351  goto lbl_5;
11352  }
11353  if( state.rstate.stage==6 )
11354  {
11355  goto lbl_6;
11356  }
11357  if( state.rstate.stage==7 )
11358  {
11359  goto lbl_7;
11360  }
11361 
11362  //
11363  // Routine body
11364  //
11365  alglib.ap.assert(alglib.ap.len(state.b)>0, "LinCGIteration: B is not initialized (you must initialize B by LinCGSetB() call");
11366  state.running = true;
11367  state.repnmv = 0;
11368  clearrfields(state, _params);
11369  updateitersdata(state, _params);
11370 
11371  //
11372  // Start 0-th iteration
11373  //
11374  for(i_=0; i_<=state.n-1;i_++)
11375  {
11376  state.rx[i_] = state.startx[i_];
11377  }
11378  for(i_=0; i_<=state.n-1;i_++)
11379  {
11380  state.x[i_] = state.rx[i_];
11381  }
11382  state.repnmv = state.repnmv+1;
11383  clearrfields(state, _params);
11384  state.needvmv = true;
11385  state.rstate.stage = 0;
11386  goto lbl_rcomm;
11387  lbl_0:
11388  state.needvmv = false;
11389  bnorm = 0;
11390  state.r2 = 0;
11391  state.meritfunction = 0;
11392  for(i=0; i<=state.n-1; i++)
11393  {
11394  state.r[i] = state.b[i]-state.mv[i];
11395  state.r2 = state.r2+state.r[i]*state.r[i];
11396  state.meritfunction = state.meritfunction+state.mv[i]*state.rx[i]-2*state.b[i]*state.rx[i];
11397  bnorm = bnorm+state.b[i]*state.b[i];
11398  }
11399  bnorm = Math.Sqrt(bnorm);
11400 
11401  //
11402  // Output first report
11403  //
11404  if( !state.xrep )
11405  {
11406  goto lbl_8;
11407  }
11408  for(i_=0; i_<=state.n-1;i_++)
11409  {
11410  state.x[i_] = state.rx[i_];
11411  }
11412  clearrfields(state, _params);
11413  state.xupdated = true;
11414  state.rstate.stage = 1;
11415  goto lbl_rcomm;
11416  lbl_1:
11417  state.xupdated = false;
11418  lbl_8:
11419 
11420  //
11421  // Is x0 a solution?
11422  //
11423  if( !math.isfinite(state.r2) || (double)(Math.Sqrt(state.r2))<=(double)(state.epsf*bnorm) )
11424  {
11425  state.running = false;
11426  if( math.isfinite(state.r2) )
11427  {
11428  state.repterminationtype = 1;
11429  }
11430  else
11431  {
11432  state.repterminationtype = -4;
11433  }
11434  result = false;
11435  return result;
11436  }
11437 
11438  //
11439  // Calculate Z and P
11440  //
11441  for(i_=0; i_<=state.n-1;i_++)
11442  {
11443  state.x[i_] = state.r[i_];
11444  }
11445  state.repnmv = state.repnmv+1;
11446  clearrfields(state, _params);
11447  state.needprec = true;
11448  state.rstate.stage = 2;
11449  goto lbl_rcomm;
11450  lbl_2:
11451  state.needprec = false;
11452  for(i=0; i<=state.n-1; i++)
11453  {
11454  state.z[i] = state.pv[i];
11455  state.p[i] = state.z[i];
11456  }
11457 
11458  //
11459  // Other iterations(1..N)
11460  //
11461  state.repiterationscount = 0;
11462  lbl_10:
11463  if( false )
11464  {
11465  goto lbl_11;
11466  }
11467  state.repiterationscount = state.repiterationscount+1;
11468 
11469  //
11470  // Calculate Alpha
11471  //
11472  for(i_=0; i_<=state.n-1;i_++)
11473  {
11474  state.x[i_] = state.p[i_];
11475  }
11476  state.repnmv = state.repnmv+1;
11477  clearrfields(state, _params);
11478  state.needvmv = true;
11479  state.rstate.stage = 3;
11480  goto lbl_rcomm;
11481  lbl_3:
11482  state.needvmv = false;
11483  if( !math.isfinite(state.vmv) || (double)(state.vmv)<=(double)(0) )
11484  {
11485 
11486  //
11487  // a) Overflow when calculating VMV
11488  // b) non-positive VMV (non-SPD matrix)
11489  //
11490  state.running = false;
11491  if( math.isfinite(state.vmv) )
11492  {
11493  state.repterminationtype = -5;
11494  }
11495  else
11496  {
11497  state.repterminationtype = -4;
11498  }
11499  result = false;
11500  return result;
11501  }
11502  state.alpha = 0;
11503  for(i=0; i<=state.n-1; i++)
11504  {
11505  state.alpha = state.alpha+state.r[i]*state.z[i];
11506  }
11507  state.alpha = state.alpha/state.vmv;
11508  if( !math.isfinite(state.alpha) )
11509  {
11510 
11511  //
11512  // Overflow when calculating Alpha
11513  //
11514  state.running = false;
11515  state.repterminationtype = -4;
11516  result = false;
11517  return result;
11518  }
11519 
11520  //
11521  // Next step toward solution
11522  //
11523  for(i=0; i<=state.n-1; i++)
11524  {
11525  state.cx[i] = state.rx[i]+state.alpha*state.p[i];
11526  }
11527 
11528  //
11529  // Calculate R:
11530  // * use recurrent relation to update R
11531  // * at every ItsBeforeRUpdate-th iteration recalculate it from scratch, using matrix-vector product
11532  // in case R grows instead of decreasing, algorithm is terminated with positive completion code
11533  //
11534  if( !(state.itsbeforerupdate==0 || state.repiterationscount%state.itsbeforerupdate!=0) )
11535  {
11536  goto lbl_12;
11537  }
11538 
11539  //
11540  // Calculate R using recurrent formula
11541  //
11542  for(i=0; i<=state.n-1; i++)
11543  {
11544  state.cr[i] = state.r[i]-state.alpha*state.mv[i];
11545  state.x[i] = state.cr[i];
11546  }
11547  goto lbl_13;
11548  lbl_12:
11549 
11550  //
11551  // Calculate R using matrix-vector multiplication
11552  //
11553  for(i_=0; i_<=state.n-1;i_++)
11554  {
11555  state.x[i_] = state.cx[i_];
11556  }
11557  state.repnmv = state.repnmv+1;
11558  clearrfields(state, _params);
11559  state.needmv = true;
11560  state.rstate.stage = 4;
11561  goto lbl_rcomm;
11562  lbl_4:
11563  state.needmv = false;
11564  for(i=0; i<=state.n-1; i++)
11565  {
11566  state.cr[i] = state.b[i]-state.mv[i];
11567  state.x[i] = state.cr[i];
11568  }
11569 
11570  //
11571  // Calculating merit function
11572  // Check emergency stopping criterion
11573  //
11574  v = 0;
11575  for(i=0; i<=state.n-1; i++)
11576  {
11577  v = v+state.mv[i]*state.cx[i]-2*state.b[i]*state.cx[i];
11578  }
11579  if( (double)(v)<(double)(state.meritfunction) )
11580  {
11581  goto lbl_14;
11582  }
11583  for(i=0; i<=state.n-1; i++)
11584  {
11585  if( !math.isfinite(state.rx[i]) )
11586  {
11587  state.running = false;
11588  state.repterminationtype = -4;
11589  result = false;
11590  return result;
11591  }
11592  }
11593 
11594  //
11595  //output last report
11596  //
11597  if( !state.xrep )
11598  {
11599  goto lbl_16;
11600  }
11601  for(i_=0; i_<=state.n-1;i_++)
11602  {
11603  state.x[i_] = state.rx[i_];
11604  }
11605  clearrfields(state, _params);
11606  state.xupdated = true;
11607  state.rstate.stage = 5;
11608  goto lbl_rcomm;
11609  lbl_5:
11610  state.xupdated = false;
11611  lbl_16:
11612  state.running = false;
11613  state.repterminationtype = 7;
11614  result = false;
11615  return result;
11616  lbl_14:
11617  state.meritfunction = v;
11618  lbl_13:
11619  for(i_=0; i_<=state.n-1;i_++)
11620  {
11621  state.rx[i_] = state.cx[i_];
11622  }
11623 
11624  //
11625  // calculating RNorm
11626  //
11627  // NOTE: monotonic decrease of R2 is not guaranteed by algorithm.
11628  //
11629  state.r2 = 0;
11630  for(i=0; i<=state.n-1; i++)
11631  {
11632  state.r2 = state.r2+state.cr[i]*state.cr[i];
11633  }
11634 
11635  //
11636  //output report
11637  //
11638  if( !state.xrep )
11639  {
11640  goto lbl_18;
11641  }
11642  for(i_=0; i_<=state.n-1;i_++)
11643  {
11644  state.x[i_] = state.rx[i_];
11645  }
11646  clearrfields(state, _params);
11647  state.xupdated = true;
11648  state.rstate.stage = 6;
11649  goto lbl_rcomm;
11650  lbl_6:
11651  state.xupdated = false;
11652  lbl_18:
11653 
11654  //
11655  //stopping criterion
11656  //achieved the required precision
11657  //
11658  if( !math.isfinite(state.r2) || (double)(Math.Sqrt(state.r2))<=(double)(state.epsf*bnorm) )
11659  {
11660  state.running = false;
11661  if( math.isfinite(state.r2) )
11662  {
11663  state.repterminationtype = 1;
11664  }
11665  else
11666  {
11667  state.repterminationtype = -4;
11668  }
11669  result = false;
11670  return result;
11671  }
11672  if( state.repiterationscount>=state.maxits && state.maxits>0 )
11673  {
11674  for(i=0; i<=state.n-1; i++)
11675  {
11676  if( !math.isfinite(state.rx[i]) )
11677  {
11678  state.running = false;
11679  state.repterminationtype = -4;
11680  result = false;
11681  return result;
11682  }
11683  }
11684 
11685  //
11686  //if X is finite number
11687  //
11688  state.running = false;
11689  state.repterminationtype = 5;
11690  result = false;
11691  return result;
11692  }
11693  for(i_=0; i_<=state.n-1;i_++)
11694  {
11695  state.x[i_] = state.cr[i_];
11696  }
11697 
11698  //
11699  //prepere of parameters for next iteration
11700  //
11701  state.repnmv = state.repnmv+1;
11702  clearrfields(state, _params);
11703  state.needprec = true;
11704  state.rstate.stage = 7;
11705  goto lbl_rcomm;
11706  lbl_7:
11707  state.needprec = false;
11708  for(i_=0; i_<=state.n-1;i_++)
11709  {
11710  state.cz[i_] = state.pv[i_];
11711  }
11712  if( state.repiterationscount%state.itsbeforerestart!=0 )
11713  {
11714  state.beta = 0;
11715  uvar = 0;
11716  for(i=0; i<=state.n-1; i++)
11717  {
11718  state.beta = state.beta+state.cz[i]*state.cr[i];
11719  uvar = uvar+state.z[i]*state.r[i];
11720  }
11721 
11722  //
11723  //check that UVar is't INF or is't zero
11724  //
11725  if( !math.isfinite(uvar) || (double)(uvar)==(double)(0) )
11726  {
11727  state.running = false;
11728  state.repterminationtype = -4;
11729  result = false;
11730  return result;
11731  }
11732 
11733  //
11734  //calculate .BETA
11735  //
11736  state.beta = state.beta/uvar;
11737 
11738  //
11739  //check that .BETA neither INF nor NaN
11740  //
11741  if( !math.isfinite(state.beta) )
11742  {
11743  state.running = false;
11744  state.repterminationtype = -1;
11745  result = false;
11746  return result;
11747  }
11748  for(i=0; i<=state.n-1; i++)
11749  {
11750  state.p[i] = state.cz[i]+state.beta*state.p[i];
11751  }
11752  }
11753  else
11754  {
11755  for(i_=0; i_<=state.n-1;i_++)
11756  {
11757  state.p[i_] = state.cz[i_];
11758  }
11759  }
11760 
11761  //
11762  //prepere data for next iteration
11763  //
11764  for(i=0; i<=state.n-1; i++)
11765  {
11766 
11767  //
11768  //write (k+1)th iteration to (k )th iteration
11769  //
11770  state.r[i] = state.cr[i];
11771  state.z[i] = state.cz[i];
11772  }
11773  goto lbl_10;
11774  lbl_11:
11775  result = false;
11776  return result;
11777 
11778  //
11779  // Saving state
11780  //
11781  lbl_rcomm:
11782  result = true;
11783  state.rstate.ia[0] = i;
11784  state.rstate.ra[0] = uvar;
11785  state.rstate.ra[1] = bnorm;
11786  state.rstate.ra[2] = v;
11787  return result;
11788  }
11789 
11790 
11791  /*************************************************************************
11792  Procedure for solution of A*x=b with sparse A.
11793 
11794  INPUT PARAMETERS:
11795  State - algorithm state
11796  A - sparse matrix in the CRS format (you MUST contvert it to
11797  CRS format by calling SparseConvertToCRS() function).
11798  IsUpper - whether upper or lower triangle of A is used:
11799  * IsUpper=True => only upper triangle is used and lower
11800  triangle is not referenced at all
11801  * IsUpper=False => only lower triangle is used and upper
11802  triangle is not referenced at all
11803  B - right part, array[N]
11804 
11805  RESULT:
11806  This function returns no result.
11807  You can get solution by calling LinCGResults()
11808 
11809  NOTE: this function uses lightweight preconditioning - multiplication by
11810  inverse of diag(A). If you want, you can turn preconditioning off by
11811  calling LinCGSetPrecUnit(). However, preconditioning cost is low and
11812  preconditioner is very important for solution of badly scaled
11813  problems.
11814 
11815  -- ALGLIB --
11816  Copyright 14.11.2011 by Bochkanov Sergey
11817  *************************************************************************/
11818  public static void lincgsolvesparse(lincgstate state,
11819  sparse.sparsematrix a,
11820  bool isupper,
11821  double[] b,
11822  alglib.xparams _params)
11823  {
11824  int n = 0;
11825  int i = 0;
11826  double v = 0;
11827  double vmv = 0;
11828  int i_ = 0;
11829 
11830  n = state.n;
11831  alglib.ap.assert(alglib.ap.len(b)>=state.n, "LinCGSetB: Length(B)<N");
11832  alglib.ap.assert(apserv.isfinitevector(b, state.n, _params), "LinCGSetB: B contains infinite or NaN values!");
11833 
11834  //
11835  // Allocate temporaries
11836  //
11837  apserv.rvectorsetlengthatleast(ref state.tmpd, n, _params);
11838 
11839  //
11840  // Compute diagonal scaling matrix D
11841  //
11842  if( state.prectype==0 )
11843  {
11844 
11845  //
11846  // Default preconditioner - inverse of matrix diagonal
11847  //
11848  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
11849  {
11850  v = sparse.sparsegetdiagonal(a, i, _params);
11851  if( (double)(v)>(double)(0) )
11852  {
11853  state.tmpd[i] = 1/Math.Sqrt(v);
11854  }
11855  else
11856  {
11857  state.tmpd[i] = 1;
11858  }
11859  }
11860  }
11861  else
11862  {
11863 
11864  //
11865  // No diagonal scaling
11866  //
11867  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
11868  {
11869  state.tmpd[i] = 1;
11870  }
11871  }
11872 
11873  //
11874  // Solve
11875  //
11876  lincgrestart(state, _params);
11877  lincgsetb(state, b, _params);
11878  while( lincgiteration(state, _params) )
11879  {
11880 
11881  //
11882  // Process different requests from optimizer
11883  //
11884  if( state.needmv )
11885  {
11886  sparse.sparsesmv(a, isupper, state.x, ref state.mv, _params);
11887  }
11888  if( state.needvmv )
11889  {
11890  sparse.sparsesmv(a, isupper, state.x, ref state.mv, _params);
11891  vmv = 0.0;
11892  for(i_=0; i_<=state.n-1;i_++)
11893  {
11894  vmv += state.x[i_]*state.mv[i_];
11895  }
11896  state.vmv = vmv;
11897  }
11898  if( state.needprec )
11899  {
11900  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
11901  {
11902  state.pv[i] = state.x[i]*math.sqr(state.tmpd[i]);
11903  }
11904  }
11905  }
11906  }
11907 
11908 
11909  /*************************************************************************
11910  CG-solver: results.
11911 
11912  This function must be called after LinCGSolve
11913 
11914  INPUT PARAMETERS:
11915  State - algorithm state
11916 
11917  OUTPUT PARAMETERS:
11918  X - array[N], solution
11919  Rep - optimization report:
11920  * Rep.TerminationType completetion code:
11921  * -5 input matrix is either not positive definite,
11922  too large or too small
11923  * -4 overflow/underflow during solution
11924  (ill conditioned problem)
11925  * 1 ||residual||<=EpsF*||b||
11926  * 5 MaxIts steps was taken
11927  * 7 rounding errors prevent further progress,
11928  best point found is returned
11929  * Rep.IterationsCount contains iterations count
11930  * NMV countains number of matrix-vector calculations
11931 
11932  -- ALGLIB --
11933  Copyright 14.11.2011 by Bochkanov Sergey
11934  *************************************************************************/
11935  public static void lincgresults(lincgstate state,
11936  ref double[] x,
11937  lincgreport rep,
11938  alglib.xparams _params)
11939  {
11940  int i_ = 0;
11941 
11942  x = new double[0];
11943 
11944  alglib.ap.assert(!state.running, "LinCGResult: you can not get result, because function LinCGIteration has been launched!");
11945  if( alglib.ap.len(x)<state.n )
11946  {
11947  x = new double[state.n];
11948  }
11949  for(i_=0; i_<=state.n-1;i_++)
11950  {
11951  x[i_] = state.rx[i_];
11952  }
11953  rep.iterationscount = state.repiterationscount;
11954  rep.nmv = state.repnmv;
11955  rep.terminationtype = state.repterminationtype;
11956  rep.r2 = state.r2;
11957  }
11958 
11959 
11960  /*************************************************************************
11961  This function sets restart frequency. By default, algorithm is restarted
11962  after N subsequent iterations.
11963 
11964  -- ALGLIB --
11965  Copyright 14.11.2011 by Bochkanov Sergey
11966  *************************************************************************/
11967  public static void lincgsetrestartfreq(lincgstate state,
11968  int srf,
11969  alglib.xparams _params)
11970  {
11971  alglib.ap.assert(!state.running, "LinCGSetRestartFreq: you can not change restart frequency when LinCGIteration() is running");
11972  alglib.ap.assert(srf>0, "LinCGSetRestartFreq: non-positive SRF");
11973  state.itsbeforerestart = srf;
11974  }
11975 
11976 
11977  /*************************************************************************
11978  This function sets frequency of residual recalculations.
11979 
11980  Algorithm updates residual r_k using iterative formula, but recalculates
11981  it from scratch after each 10 iterations. It is done to avoid accumulation
11982  of numerical errors and to stop algorithm when r_k starts to grow.
11983 
11984  Such low update frequence (1/10) gives very little overhead, but makes
11985  algorithm a bit more robust against numerical errors. However, you may
11986  change it
11987 
11988  INPUT PARAMETERS:
11989  Freq - desired update frequency, Freq>=0.
11990  Zero value means that no updates will be done.
11991 
11992  -- ALGLIB --
11993  Copyright 14.11.2011 by Bochkanov Sergey
11994  *************************************************************************/
11995  public static void lincgsetrupdatefreq(lincgstate state,
11996  int freq,
11997  alglib.xparams _params)
11998  {
11999  alglib.ap.assert(!state.running, "LinCGSetRUpdateFreq: you can not change update frequency when LinCGIteration() is running");
12000  alglib.ap.assert(freq>=0, "LinCGSetRUpdateFreq: non-positive Freq");
12001  state.itsbeforerupdate = freq;
12002  }
12003 
12004 
12005  /*************************************************************************
12006  This function turns on/off reporting.
12007 
12008  INPUT PARAMETERS:

12010  NeedXRep- whether iteration reports are needed or not
12011 
12012  If NeedXRep is True, algorithm will call rep() callback function if it is
12013  provided to MinCGOptimize().
12014 
12015  -- ALGLIB --
12016  Copyright 14.11.2011 by Bochkanov Sergey
12017  *************************************************************************/
12018  public static void lincgsetxrep(lincgstate state,
12019  bool needxrep,

12021  {
12022  state.xrep = needxrep;
12023  }

12026  /*************************************************************************
12027  Procedure for restart function LinCGIteration
12028 
12029  -- ALGLIB --
12030  Copyright 14.11.2011 by Bochkanov Sergey
12031  *************************************************************************/
12032  public static void lincgrestart(lincgstate state,
12033  alglib.xparams _params)
12034  {
12035  state.rstate.ia = new int[0+1];
12036  state.rstate.ra = new double[2+1];
12037  state.rstate.stage = -1;
12038  clearrfields(state, _params);
12039  }

12043  Clears request fileds (to be sure that we don't forgot to clear something)

12046  alglib.xparams _params)
12047  {

12049  state.needmv = false;
12050  state.needmtv = false;
12051  state.needmv2 = false;
12052  state.needvmv = false;
12053  state.needprec = false;
12054  }
12055 
12056 
12057  /*************************************************************************

12059  *************************************************************************/
12060  private static void updateitersdata(lincgstate state,

12062  {
12063  state.repiterationscount = 0;
12064  state.repnmv = 0;
12065  state.repterminationtype = 0;
12066  }
12067 
12068 
12069  }
12070 }
